<TEXT>
the new us ambassador to britain henry catto 
arrived sunday promising to work on further strengthening the close 
ties between the two countries 
the american people cherish our nations special relationship 
with the uk the texas native said after arriving at londons 
heathrow airport clutching a creamcolored stetson hat 
i am honored to be a trustee of that valued partnership and 
promise to maintain and enhance it 
president bush chose catto the former ambassador to el 
salvador white house chief of protocol and assistant secretary of 
defense for public affairs to succeed charles price ii price an 
appointee of president reagan returned to his native kansas city 
