the issue of the environment has by now become an explosive 
and decisive cutting edge in mainstream politics writes pollster 
louis harris in a contributing essay to the study 
one need go no further than the march 24 oil spill in alaska and 
the publics perception of inept and confusing attempts by 
government and industry to deal with it to show the interest that 
americans have in the environment suggest the studys authors 
in the aftermath of the spill bushs positive rating on 
